  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse the <strong>quinoa </strong>under <strong>cold running water</strong>, then add it to a pot with a lid with 180ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [360ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and leave to steam-dry, uncovered</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1610453856852-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1610453856852-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1610453856852-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1610453856852-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1610453856852-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> into large pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato </strong>to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the sweet potato is fork tender, once done, transfer the sweet potato to a plate and mash it out flat to help it cool down, reserve the bowl</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610453880592-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610453880592-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610453880592-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610453880592-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610453880592-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato is in the microwave, cut the <strong>broccoli</strong> into small florets and cut the stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>broccoli florets </strong>and<strong> chopped stem </strong>to a baking tray (use <strong>baking paper</strong> to avoid mess!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610453915271-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610453915271-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610453915271-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610453915271-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610453915271-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
